I see the issue now. The `isExtendedFreeSwapAllowed` function checks for freeswap **special tiles** on the board — but in `executeSwap`, `hasFreeSwap` (line 496) also detects these special tiles. So when `hasFreeSwap` is true, the swap doesn't cost a move (line 514), regardless of whether the "swap" power-up is active.

But re-reading the user's message: the issue is that `isExtendedFreeSwapAllowed` (which enables non-adjacent row/col swaps) should only apply to freeswap **special tiles**, not when the "swap" **power-up button** is active. Let me verify — does the swap power-up already bypass `isExtendedFreeSwapAllowed`?

Looking at `trySwap` line 566-568:
```js
const isPowerUpSwap = !isAdjacentSwap && (game.activePowerUp === "swap" || game.activePowerUp === "teleport");
if (!isAdjacentSwap && !allowExtendedFreeSwap && !allowTeleportSwap && !isPowerUpSwap) {
    return false;
}
```

The swap power-up already has its own path (`isPowerUpSwap`), separate from `allowExtendedFreeSwap`. And `isExtendedFreeSwapAllowed` already only checks for special tiles.

Could the user be saying that the `hasFreeSwap` variable in `executeSwap` shouldn't skip move cost when a swap power-up is active? Let me check if there's an interaction issue where using the swap power-up on a freeswap special tile makes it "free" (no move cost) when it shouldn't be.

Looking at line 514: `if (!isSwapPowerUp && !isTeleportPowerUp && !hasFreeSwap && !hasTeleport)` — if you use the swap power-up on a freeswap tile, `isSwapPowerUp` is true so moves won't increment anyway (the power-up is consumed instead). That seems fine.

Let me ask for clarification since the current code already separates these concerns.

